<p>At the age of 5, Carter was diagnosed with <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/3-facts-about-acute-lymphocytic-leukemia-in-children/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">T-cell leukemia</a> and was treated Mayo Clinic Children's. Carter is now 17 years old and remembers the 2014 visit from superheroes when he was hospitalized.&amp;nbsp;</p>



